[2
Date: Tue, 19 May 1998 01:03:46 +0200
From: Trine & Peter Jantzen <jantzen@dadlnet.dk>
Source: Bovine Spongiform Encephalopathy <BSE-L@RZ.UNI-KARLSRUHE.DE>

Not only Hong Kong and Netherlands have experiences with a (only one?) batch
of the diagnosticum "Amerscan Pulminate II Agent". In Denmark more than 400
patients were examined with this medicament from June-July 1997 up until
November-December 1997. The Danish Parliament decided to inform all
patients. This decision was carried out by the hospitals.
